Looks like there is a bug with Shared transition, to reproduce but writing steps here.
1) Create a new activity for example activity is TestActivity

   package com.example.android.activityscenetransitionbasic;
   import android.app.Activity;
   public class TestActivity extends Activity {
   }
   // add this activity in manifest file 
   <activity android:name=".TestActivity" />
 
 2) Modify layout details.xml
 provide an id for the last textview which is after textview_title, name this id as description
 android:id="@+id/description"
 
 3) Now modify DetailsActivity onCreate like below
 
 @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.details);

        // Retrieve the correct Item instance, using the ID provided in the Intent
        mItem = Item.getItem(getIntent().getIntExtra(EXTRA_PARAM_ID, 0));

        mHeaderImageView = (ImageView) findViewById(R.id.imageview_header);
        mHeaderTitle = (TextView) findViewById(R.id.textview_title);
        description = (TextView) findViewById(R.id.description);

        // BEGIN_INCLUDE(detail_set_view_name)
        /**
         * Set the name of the view's which will be transition to, using the static values above.
         * This could be done in the layout XML, but exposing it via static variables allows easy
         * querying from other Activities
         */
        ViewCompat.setTransitionName(mHeaderImageView, VIEW_NAME_HEADER_IMAGE);
       // ViewCompat.setTransitionName(mHeaderTitle, VIEW_NAME_HEADER_TITLE);
        // END_INCLUDE(detail_set_view_name)

        mHeaderImageView.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
            @Override
            public void onClick(View v) {
                startActivity(new Intent(DetailActivity.this,TestActivity.class));
            }
        });
        description.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
            @Override
            public void onClick(View v) {
                mHeaderTitle.setVisibility(View.GONE);
            }
        });
        loadItem();
    }
    
    4) Run the app, then select any item from the grid, after that click on description textView. then tap on imageview_header, 
    it will launch another blank activity.
    
    5) Press back button and observe the behavior.
    
    This should be fixed ASAP, because of this issue many of us stopped using shared transition.
 
